Malaysia Stocks: KL Kepong, KNM Group, Lion Diversified, Sime

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-03-04T09:21:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/malaysia-stocks-kl-kepong-knm-group-lion-diversified-sime.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 5 p.m. close in  Kuala
Lumpur .  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index rose 15.73, or 1 percent,
to 1,522.61, its biggest advance since Jan. 4. The gauge has
gained 2.2 percent this week, the steepest increase since Jan. 7.  Plantation stocks:  Kuala Lumpur Kepong Bhd. (KLK)  Bhd
led plantation stocks higher after  palm oil  advanced, headed for
its first weekly increase in three weeks. Kepong shares rose 2.9
percent to 21.10 ringgit, the largest gain since Feb. 7.  Sime
Darby Bhd. (SIME)   added 1 percent to 9.17 ringgit and IOI
Corp. (IOI MK) advanced 2.9 percent to 5.73 ringgit.    KNM Group Bhd. (KNMG)  , an oil and gas services provider,
jumped 7.9 percent to 2.59 ringgit, the most since Dec. 22. The
company secured new orders amounting to 693 million ringgit
($229 million) this year, in line with “improved sentiment” in
the global industry, according to a company statement.        Lion Diversified Holdings Bhd. (LDHB)  , an investment
group, rose 5.9 percent to 45 sen, the largest gain since Aug. 9.
The company agreed to form a venture with  Lion Forest Industries
Bhd. (POS)   and Lion Industries Corp. (LLB MK) for a blast
furnace project costing $1.06 billion, according to a statement.
Lion Forest advanced 0.6 percent to 1.80 ringgit. Lion
Industries dropped 3 percent to 1.63 ringgit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
